OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1774023076
OL,3,CIllegal waste dumps to be cleared amid
OL,4,Ccrackdown on fly-tipping
OL,6,FThe rubbish in Bickershaw, Wigan,
OL,7,Femerged in summer 2025 when 25,000
OL,8,Ftonnes of waste was burned in a week-
OL,9,Flong fire.
OL,11,FLocals reported multiple lorries
OL,12,Fcarrying rubbish to the site over
OL,13,Fseveral months starting in January
OL,14,F2025.
OL,16,FThe waste piled up to 20 metres high
OL,17,Fand images showed bin bags full of
OL,18,Fhousehold rubbish containing harmful
OL,19,Fchemicals and plastics.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1774023076
OL,3,CIllegal waste dumps to be cleared amid
OL,4,Ccrackdown on fly-tipping
OL,6,FNearby schools were forced to close
OL,7,Fand a criminal investigation is
OL,8,Funderway to find out who is
OL,9,Fresponsible.
OL,11,FThe dump is based at a former
OL,12,Fscrapyard on Bolton House Road. Other
OL,13,Fwaste sites in Hyndburn, Lancashire
OL,14,Fwill already be cleaned up, the
OL,15,FEnvironment Agency confirmed.
OL,17,FIn February, 2026, Makerfield MP Josh
OL,18,FSimons called on the King's estate,
OL,19,Fwhich owns some of the land, to pay a
OL,20,Fportion of the estimated #4.5million
OL,21,Fbill.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1774023076
OL,3,CIllegal waste dumps to be cleared amid
OL,4,Ccrackdown on fly-tipping
OL,6,FIn addition to the clean up costs, the
OL,7,Fgovernment has pledged an additional
OL,8,F#45m for the Environment Agency to
OL,9,Fspend on waste crime enforcement over
OL,10,Fthe next three financial years, on top
OL,11,Fof the #5.6 million increase for this
OL,12,Ffinancial year announced previously.
OL,14,FThe new Waste Crime Action Plan is
OL,15,Fsaid to involve a "zero-tolerance
OL,16,Fapproach" by closing loopholes and
OL,17,Fequipping regulators with the tools
OL,18,Fthey need to stop waste criminals.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
